OASISFormat: 0.3
Name: gg
Version: 0.9.0
Synopsis: Basic types for computer graphics in OCaml
Authors: Daniel Bünzli <daniel.buenzli at erratique.ch>, Edwin Török <edwin at etorok.net>
Copyrights: (c) 2013 Daniel C. Bünzli and Edwin Török
License: BSD3
Homepage: http://erratique.ch/software/gg
Description:
 Gg provides basic support for computer graphics programming in
 OCaml. It defines types for vectors, matrices, quaternions, colors,
 color spaces, axis aligned boxes and raster data.
 .
 Gg is made of a single, independent, module and distributed under
 the BSD3 license.

